**Set up a profile:**

Error

![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAYAAAAfFcSJAAAADUlEQVR4XmP4//8/AwAI/AL+GwXmLwAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==)

This usually means the installer (subiquity with curtin) had trouble during the **APT package configuration step**. Common causes are:

1\. You did not check the **Unblock** security option in the properties of the Ubuntu Server file. 2. **No internet connection** (APT cannot fetch required packages).

3\. **Bad mirror or repo unreachable** (network timeout or blocked domain).

4\. **Corrupted ISO** (installer cannot unpack packages).

5\. **Insufficient disk space or partitioning issue**.

**Virtual machine misconfiguration** (if using VMware, VirtualBox, Hyper-V, etc.  sometimes storage controllers cause problems).

Check these problems one by one, and after solving each problem, start again from Step 4 (Start the virtual machine).
